From e526c067bcae0d551c9c0043c5cadb43b43756c8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ram <chan2006@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 16:16:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add dedicated Brownfield section to the public landing page
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Greenfield had a full showcase on the arch.nexplan.io landing page
(hero, 4-agent pipeline visual, feature grid, live demo terminal) —
Brownfield had none, just a single unexplained bullet buried in the
Team-plan pricing card ('All clouds + Brownfield scan').

Added a new #brownfield section, placed between Knowledge Base and
Cloud Support, mirroring Greenfield's exact visual treatment:
- 4-step pipeline visual (Scanner, Auditor, Planner, Engineer),
  reusing the existing .pipeline/.pipe-step CSS classes
- 3 feature cards (full infra audit, phased migration plan,
  cost before/after), reusing the existing .feat-grid/.feat-card
  classes
- Labelled 'Team plan & up' so free/Pro visitors aren't misled
  about what's included
- Added a 'Brownfield' link to the nav bar (#how-it-works,
  #features, #brownfield, #pricing, #faq)

No new CSS was written — every class reused already exists in the
stylesheet, so this is purely additive markup. Verified: next build
succeeds (20/20 pages), section order confirmed via grep (Knowledge
Base -> Brownfield -> Cloud Support -> Pricing), <section>/<div>
tag counts balanced (9/9, 263/263).
---
 public/landing.html | 58 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 58 insertions(+)

diff --git a/public/landing.html b/public/landing.html
index 5a1e4a4..4098f17 100644
--- a/public/landing.html
+++ b/public/landing.html
@@ -270,6 +270,7 @@ footer nav.footer-links{position:static !important;display:flex !important;flex-
     <div class="nav-links">
       <a href="#how-it-works">How it works</a>
       <a href="#features">Features</a>
+      <a href="#brownfield">Brownfield</a>
       <a href="#pricing">Pricing</a>
       <a href="#faq">FAQ</a>
     </div>
@@ -554,6 +555,63 @@ footer nav.footer-links{position:static !important;display:flex !important;flex-
   </div>
 </section>
 
+<!-- BROWNFIELD MIGRATION -->
+<section id="brownfield" class="pipeline-bg">
+  <div class="container">
+    <div class="center">
+      <div class="sec-label">Brownfield migration · Team plan &amp; up</div>
+      <h2 class="sec-title">Already on the cloud? Modernise it — don't rebuild it.</h2>
+      <p class="sec-sub">Paste your existing Terraform, a state file, or just describe your current setup. ArchAI scans it, audits it, plans the migration, and hands you modernised, ready-to-deploy Terraform for your target cloud.</p>
+    </div>
+    <div class="pipeline">
+      <div class="pipe-step">
+        <span class="pipe-icon">🔍</span>
+        <div class="pipe-num">01</div>
+        <div class="pipe-name">Scanner</div>
+        <p class="pipe-desc">Reads your existing Terraform, .tfstate, or plain-English description and maps every resource, its config, and known issues.</p>
+        <div class="pipe-arrow">→</div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="pipe-step">
+        <span class="pipe-icon">🛡️</span>
+        <div class="pipe-num">02</div>
+        <div class="pipe-name">Auditor</div>
+        <p class="pipe-desc">Flags security exposures, deprecated instance types, and wasted spend. Every finding scored critical to low, with a compliance score out of 100.</p>
+        <div class="pipe-arrow">→</div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="pipe-step">
+        <span class="pipe-icon">🗺️</span>
+        <div class="pipe-num">03</div>
+        <div class="pipe-name">Planner</div>
+        <p class="pipe-desc">Builds a phased migration plan — sequenced by risk, with time estimates and before/after cost projections. No big-bang rewrites.</p>
+        <div class="pipe-arrow">→</div>
+      </div>
+      <div class="pipe-step">
+        <span class="pipe-icon">⚙️</span>
+        <div class="pipe-num">04</div>
+        <div class="pipe-name">Engineer</div>
+        <p class="pipe-desc">Generates modernised, deploy-ready Terraform for your target cloud — carrying over your Knowledge Base standards automatically.</p>
+      </div>
+    </div>
+    <div class="feat-grid" style="margin-top:32px">
+      <article class="feat-card">
+        <span class="feat-emoji">🔎</span>
+        <h3 class="feat-title">Full infrastructure audit</h3>
+        <p class="feat-desc">Every existing resource checked for public exposure, missing encryption, deprecated instance types, and hardcoded secrets — with a compliance score you can track over time.</p>
+      </article>
+      <article class="feat-card">
+        <span class="feat-emoji">🗓️</span>
+        <h3 class="feat-title">Phased migration plan</h3>
+        <p class="feat-desc">Risk-scored phases with estimated hours per step. Know exactly what changes, in what order, and how long it takes — before you touch a single resource.</p>
+      </article>
+      <article class="feat-card">
+        <span class="feat-emoji">💵</span>
+        <h3 class="feat-title">Cost before vs. after</h3>
+        <p class="feat-desc">See projected monthly savings side by side with your current spend, plus every cost-waste finding identified during the audit.</p>
+      </article>
+    </div>
+  </div>
+</section>
+
 <!-- CLOUD SUPPORT -->
 <section class="clouds-bg">
   <div class="container">
